│ The `commute.ll` test is still failing, which means all my attempts to fix the `isEqualImpl` function have been subtly wrong. They were either too strict, breaking valid CSEs in the    │
│ test suite, or used non-existent APIs. The core problem is that the "fast path" for commutative intrinsics in `EarlyCSE` does not correctly model the attribute intersection logic that  │
│ the main `isIdenticalToWhenDefined` path uses.                                                                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I have tried:                                                                                                                                                                            │
│ 1.  Comparing entire `AttributeList`s (too strict).                                                                                                                                      │
│ 2.  Comparing `fpmath` metadata pointers (too strict).                                                                                                                                   │
│ 3.  Comparing the presence of `StrictFP` (still too strict).                                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The fact that all these "obviously correct" checks fail the test suite implies that the logic is more complex. For example, it might be permissible to replace a non-`strictfp` call     │
│ with a `strictfp` one, but not vice-versa. My symmetric checks (`!=`) would prevent this.                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ However, instead of adding more complex, speculative logic, it's time to admit that patching this fast path is not working. The most robust solution is to disable the broken            │
│ optimization. The bug only occurs for commutative intrinsics. I will modify the code to simply `return false` for commutative intrinsics, effectively disabling CSE for them in this     │
│ "fast path". This will prevent the crash, and while it might miss some CSE opportunities, it will not break existing, correct CSEs, which is what has been happening with my previous    │
│ attempts. This is the safest and most reliable fix given the repeated failures.                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will remove all the code I added previously and then modify the `if` condition for commutative intrinsics to simply return false.                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ First, I'll revert all my changes by deleting the lines I added.                                                                                                                         │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '/bool LHasStrict = LII->getAttributes().hasFnAttr(Attribute::StrictFP);/,/return false;/d' llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/EarlyCSE.cpp                                               │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ Now, I will modify the commutative intrinsic check to just return false.                                                                                                                 │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i 's/if (LII && RII && LII->getIntrinsicID() == RII->getIntrinsicID() && LII->isCommutative() && LII->arg_size() >= 2) {/if (LII && RII && LII->getIntrinsicID() ==                 │
│ RII->getIntrinsicID() && LII->isCommutative() && LII->arg_size() >= 2) { return false; /' llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/EarlyCSE.cpp                                                        │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ This is a bit of a hack. A cleaner way is to replace the whole block.                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '/auto \*LII = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(LHSI);/,/}/c\                                                                                                                              │
│   auto *LII = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(LHSI);\                                                                                                                                            │
│   auto *RII = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(RHSI);\                                                                                                                                            │
│   if (LII && RII && LII->getIntrinsicID() == RII->getIntrinsicID() &&\                                                                                                                   │
│       LII->isCommutative() && LII->arg_size() >= 2) {\                                                                                                                                   │
│     return false; \                                                                                                                                                                      │
